OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA dry morning with plenty of
OL,6,Flong sunny periods. Remaining dry in
OL,7,Fthe afternoon but cloud thickening
OL,8,Fwith more limited brighter spells.
OL,9,FWinds light at first but becoming
OL,10,Fbreezy through the afternoon.
OL,11,
OL,12,CTonight:FA cloudy night with rain
OL,13,Fspreading northeastwards and becoming
OL,14,Fheavy at times. Rain clearing western
OL,15,FAberdeenshire by morning. Winds
OL,16,Fbecoming strong with coastal gales
OL,17,Fbefore easing later in the night.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
